                Assembly
              </span> <span style="text-transform: uppercase">March 19, 2026</span><br/></td></tr></tbody><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Bill
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 2303</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Member Muratsuchi<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>February 19, 2026</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> An act to add Section 33318.3 to the Education Code, relating to school accountability. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">AB 2303, as amended, Muratsuchi.
                          School accountability:<font color="#B30000"><strike> data systems: reporting.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> local educational agencies: required plans and reports.</i></font></span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law requires the governing board of each school district to adopt a local control and accountability plan (LCAP) using a template adopted by the State Board of Education. Existing law requires the governing board of each school district to update its LCAP before July 1 of each year and requires that annual update to be developed using a template adopted by the state board.</div><font color="#B30000"><strike><p style="display:inline;"><s>Existing law establishes the California Longitudinal Pupil Achievement Data System (CalPADS) and requires, among other things, the State Department of Education, in consultation with the Department of Finance and the Legislative Analyst’s Office, to include data on a quarterly rate of pupil attendance in the system, if federal funds are received for this purpose.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would require the Legislative Analyst’s Office to<font color="#B30000"><strike>			 review existing required reports, planning documents, and deadlines associated with those reports and documents, and to</strike></font> prepare a report that includes recommendations<font color="#B30000"><strike> to reduce and remove</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> for (1) reducing and removing</i></font> conflicting or redundant reports and reporting deadlines, as provided,<font color="#B30000"><strike> recommendations for</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> (2)</i></font> a statewide data submission portal, as provided, and<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> (3)</i></font>
			 a statewide<font color="#B30000"><strike> accountability</strike></font> calendar that identifies<font color="#B30000"><strike> all recommended reporting deadlines.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
			 the deadlines of all plans and reports required to be submitted by school districts, county offices of education, or charter schools, as provided.</i></font> The bill would require the Legislative Analyst’s Office, on or before<font color="#B30000"><strike> July 1, 2027,</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> January 1, 2028,</i></font> to submit the report to the appropriate budget and policy committees of the Legislature and to the<font color="#B30000"><strike> Governor. The bill would also require the State Department of Education, on or before July 1 of each year thereafter, to update the statewide accountability calendar.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> </i></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>Governor
			 and, in preparing the report, to solicit and incorporate feedback from statewide organizations, as provided. </i></font></div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="vote">
      Vote:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">MAJORITY</span>  </span><span id="appropriation">
      Appropriation:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">YES</span>  </span><span id="localprogram">
      Local Program:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><div id="bill"><div style=" text-transform: uppercase"><h2 style=" text-align: left;">The people of the State of California do enact as follows:</h2><br/></div><div id="s10.9226691371006245"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;">SECTION 1.</h3> Section 33318.3 is added to the Education Code, to read:</div><div><div id="id_C62A3FD4-8284-4CD8-8612-465D285E9576"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">33318.3.</h6> (a) The Legislature finds and declares both of the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) The multiplicity of procedures, portals, and timelines for submission of required compliance and expenditure reports<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> and plans</i></font> by local educational agencies imposes burdens on the time, human resources, and funding of public schools.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) Better aligned and coherent reporting mechanisms and methodologies will reduce these burdens, result in more complete, uniform, and quality data, and further the purposes of the statewide system of support.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) The purpose of this section is to accomplish both of the following goals:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) Reduce the duplication and burden of<font color="#B30000"><strike> reporting requirements</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> required plans and reports</i></font> on local educational agencies.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) Improve coherence in the statewide system of support and the quality and utility of information.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(c) In order to accomplish the goals specified in subdivision (b), the Legislative Analyst’s<font color="#B30000"><strike> Office, shall do</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
						Office shall prepare a report that includes recommendations for</i></font> all of the following:</div><font color="#B30000"><strike><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(1)<span class="EnSpace"/>Review existing required reports and planning documents, including, but not limited to, the California Longitudinal Pupil Achievement Data System and the reporting requirements of a local control and accountability plan.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(2)<span class="EnSpace"/>Review
						reporting deadlines for local educational agencies across and within state agencies, departments, and offices.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(3)<span class="EnSpace"/>(A)<span class="EnSpace"/>Prepare a report that includes all of the following:</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 4em;">(i)<span class="EnSpace"/>Recommendations to reduce and remove conflicting</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) Reducing and removing conflicting</i></font> or redundant reports and reporting deadlines to allow local educational agencies sufficient time to plan, prepare for, and meet the
						reporting requirements.</div><font color="#B30000"><strike><s><p style="margin-left: 4em;">(ii)<span class="EnSpace"/>(I)<span class="EnSpace"/>Recommendations for a</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) (A) A</i></font> statewide data submission portal that would allow a local educational agency to enter<font color="#B30000"><strike> reporting</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> plan or report</i></font> information once, and that could be used to<font color="#B30000"><strike> generate</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
						autopopulate fields of</i></font> multiple<font color="#B30000"><strike> reports.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> plans or reports, including, but not limited to, all of the following:</i></font></div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 4em;">(i) The data fields that should be included in the portal.</div></i></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 4em;">(ii) The reports that could be populated by data in the portal.</div></i></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 4em;">(iii) Which state entities are best suited to
						create, host, and maintain the portal.</div></i></font><font color="#B30000"><strike><s><p style="margin-left: 5.5em;">(II)</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(B)</i></font> In preparing the recommendations pursuant to<font color="#B30000"><strike>						subclause (I),</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> subparagraph (A),</i></font> the Legislative Analyst’s Office shall confer with the department and<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> other state agencies that operate similar data portals or may be able to create a data portal and shall</i></font> research data
						submission portals in use in other states.</div><font color="#B30000"><strike><s><p style="margin-left: 4em;">(iii)</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3)</i></font> A statewide<font color="#B30000"><strike> reporting</strike></font> calendar that identifies<font color="#B30000"><strike> all</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
						the</i></font> deadlines<font color="#B30000"><strike> recommended for retention pursuant to clause (i).</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> of all plans and reports required to be submitted by local educational agencies. These recommendations shall include, but not be limited to, all of the following:</i></font></div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(A) The content that should be included in the calendar.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(B) Which entities are best suited to create, host, and maintain the calendar.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(C) The frequency and methods that should be used to update the calendar.</div></i></font><font color="#B30000"><strike><s><p style="margin-left: 2.5em;">(B)</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(d)</i></font> In preparing the report described in<font color="#B30000"><strike> subparagraph (A),</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
						subdivision (c),</i></font> the Legislative Analyst’s Office shall solicit and incorporate feedback from statewide organizations, including, but not limited to, organizations representing the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 4em;">(i) School boards.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 4em;">(ii) County offices of education.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 4em;">(iii) School administrators.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 4em;">(iv) School business officers.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 4em;">(v) Small school districts.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 4em;">(vi) Medium-sized school districts.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 4em;">(vii) Large school districts.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 4em;">(viii) Labor unions.</div><font color="#B30000"><strike><p style="display:inline;"><s>(d)</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(e)</i></font> (1) On or before<font color="#B30000"><strike> July 1, 2027,</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> January 1, 2028,</i></font> the Legislative Analyst’s Office shall submit the report prepared pursuant to<font color="#B30000"><strike> paragraph (3) of</strike></font> subdivision (c) to the appropriate budget and policy committees of the Legislature and to the Governor.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) The report submitted pursuant to paragraph (1) shall be submitted in compliance with section 9795 of the Government Code.</div><font color="#B30000"><strike><p style="display:inline;"><s>(e)<span class="EnSpace"/>On or before July 1, 2028, and on or before July 1 of each year thereafter, the department shall update the statewide
						reporting calendar.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(f) For purposes of this section, “local educational agency”
						means a school district, county office of education, or charter school.</div></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></body></html>
